<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-03-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-03-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="393" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d393">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 815.00/1188.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Tegucigalpa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-03-14"><hi rend="italic">March 14,
                                1911</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. McCreery says he is advised by the President of Honduras that
                            Congress has accepted the resignation of the Vice President, that Gen.
                            Rafael López Gutiérrez has been given command, and that Gen. Carias has
                            ordered his troops to Comayagua from Santa Cruz in accordance with peace
                            agreement.</p>
                    </div>
